{{Sidebar("Glossary")}}

`flex` is a value of the CSS {{cssxref("display")}} property. Along with `inline-flex`, it causes the element it applies to become a {{glossary("flex container")}}, and the element's children to each become a {{glossary("flex item")}}. The items then participate in flex layout, and all of the properties defined in the [CSS flexible box layout module](/blog/Web/CSS/CSS_flexible_box_layout) may be applied.

There is also a {{cssxref("flex")}} property, which is a shorthand for the flexbox properties {{cssxref("flex-grow")}}, {{cssxref("flex-shrink")}} and {{cssxref("flex-basis")}}. This property is only applicable to flex containers.

In addition [`<flex>`](/blog/Web/CSS/flex_value) can refer to a [flexible length](/blog/Web/CSS/flex_value) in CSS Grid Layout.

